    "Body": " Mothership Foundation is looking for an Operations Architect who will design, implement and assume ownership of Mothership's application infrastructure including our digital asset exchange with the highest possible requirements for security, performance and reliability. As an integral member of our team, the Operations Architect ensures uptime, data integrity, and strict company-wide security monitoring. You have extensive experience with production Linux operations and current security best practices in cloud-hosted clusters. Background in cryptocurrency and blockchain with experience operating blockchain nodes is extremely relevant. RESPONSIBILITIES \u2022 Work on project\u2019s architecture together with dev team leads \u2022 Improve and evolve a CI/CD pipeline using industry standards \u2022 Design security framework for the whole project \u2022 Build a fault tolerant system with a high SLA \u2022 Evaluates, deploys and configures monitoring, alerting and auditing tools \u2022 Troubleshoot deployment and infrastructure issues \u2022 Leverage Docker and containerisation for faster deployments and higher reliability REQUIREMENTS \u2022 6+ years of Linux administration with high volume, high availability distributed systems \u2022 Expert working knowledge and experience with Google Cloud Platform \u2022 Expert working knowledge and experience with Docker and Kubernetes \u2022 Node.js and Golang applications deployment experience with the best practice know-how \u2022 Deep understanding of IP Networking - routing, tunnels/VPN, firewalls & NAT \u2022 Extensive knowledge of active security monitoring, IDS, recovery planning \u2022 Bonus: Knowledge of blockchain nodes setup is a plus \u2022 Excellent troubleshooting, debugging, communication and documentation skills \u2022 Ability to perform well in a fast-paced environment WHY MOTHERSHIP? \u2022 Both of the Mothership founders are engineers with a solid background in web and mobile app development. You'll be able to collaborate with them and learn a lot. \u2022 We all came from startups and enterprises, and are excited to work together and build great things! \u2022 We operate as a mixed remote and on-site teams, spread across the globe, with our headquarters in Tallinn, Estonia. \u2022 We believe that blockchain technology, cryptocurrencies, and decentralised systems will change the world. And we are part of it. WHAT YOU'LL GET \u2022 Competitive salary \u2022 Generous stock options \u2022 Opportunity to make a huge impact on our products \u2022 Visa sponsorship and relocation package \u2022 Hangouts in Tallinn \u2022 Conference passes \u2022 All the books you can read \u2022 A smart and motivated team from all over the world in a well-funded startup LOCATION Mothership is based in Tallinn, Estonia. It's a quiet and beautiful city with an excellent infrastructure. We offer a relocation package and will help you get a visa. Besides this, remote employees are first-class citizens in our company; we embrace the remote development culture. PLEASE APPLY HERE: https://jobs.lever.co/mothership/079c43e2-42a2-4572-846a-9974b1bd46e8?lever-origin=applied&lever-source%5B%5D=CryptoJobs Skills Linux, Google Cloud, Docker, Kubernetes, NodeJS/Golang deployment, Security Compensation Let's discuss numbers during the interview + Equity ", 
